recalls.Summary:
Subaru of America, Inc. (Subaru) is recalling certain 2009-2013 Forester, 2003-2006 Baja, 2004-2011 Impreza, 2004-2014 WRX (including STI), 2003-2014 Legacy and Outback, and 2006 Saab 9-2X vehicles originally sold, or ever registered, in the states of Arizona, Arkansas, Delaware, District of Columbia, Illinois, Indiana, Kansas, Kentucky, Maryland, Missouri, Nebraska, Nevada, New Jersey, New Mexico, North Carolina, Ohio, Oklahoma, Pennsylvania, Tennessee, Virginia, and West Virginia or "Zone B."  

These vehicles had their passenger frontal air bag inflators previously replaced under a prior recall using inflators of the same design.  The inflators may explode due to propellant degradation occurring after long-term exposure to high absolute humidity, temperature and temperature cycling.
recalls.Consequence: An inflator explosion may result in sharp metal fragments striking the driver or other occupants resulting in serious injury or death.
recalls.Remedy: Subaru will notify their owners.  General Motors will notify Saab owners.  Dealers will replace the passenger air bag inflators, free of charge.  The recall began January 7, 2020.  Subaru owners may contact Subaru customer service at 1-844-373-6614.  Saab owners may contact the Saab Customer Assistance Center at 1-800-955-9007.  Subaru's number for this recall is TKB-20.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

SUBARU IS RECALLING CERTAIN MODEL YEAR 2002-2007 IMPREZA, MODEL YEAR 2003-2008 FORESTER, AND MODEL YEAR 2005-2006 SAAB 9-2X VEHICLES MANUFACTURED FROM SEPTEMBER 5, 2000 THROUGH NOVEMBER 26, 2007 ORIGINALLY SOLD, OR CURRENTLY REGISTERED IN,  MASSACHUSETTS, MARYLAND, MICHIGAN, NEW HAMPSHIRE, NEW YORK, PENNSYLVANIA,  VERMONT, WISCONSIN, CONNECTICUT, DELAWARE, IOWA, ILLINOIS, INDIANA, MAINE, MINNESOTA, MISSOURI, NEW JERSEY, OHIO, RHODE ISLAND, WEST VIRGINIA AND THE DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA.
THE FRONT LOWER CONTROL ARMS MAY BREAK AT THE HANGER BRACKETS DUE TO CORROSION IF THE HANGER BRACKET IS EXPOSED TO SALTY AND HUMID ENVIRONMENTS SUCH AS ROADS CONTAINING SNOW MELTING AGENT.
recalls.Consequence: A BROKEN CONTROL ARM CAN RESULT IN THE LOSS OF CONTROL OF THE VEHICLE, INCREASING THE RISK OF A CRASH.
recalls.Remedy: SUBARU WILL HANDLE THEIR VEHICLES AND SAAB WILL HANDLE THEIRS.  DEALERS WILL INSPECT THE DEGREE OF CORROSION OF THE FRONT LOWER CONTROL ARMS, AND WILL EITHER RUSTPROOF OR REPLACE THEM.  THIS SERVICE WILL BE PERFORMED FREE OF CHARGE.  THE SAFETY RECALL IS EXPECTED TO BEGIN DURING DECEMBER 2011.  OWNERS MAY CONTACT SUBARU AT 1-800-782-2783. OWNERS MAY CONTACT SAAB AT 1-800-955-9007.
recalls.Notes: THIS IS SUBARU'S SAFETY RECALL NUMBER WVX-34. OWNERS MAY ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S VEHICLE SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), OR GO TO HTTP://WWW.SAFERCAR.GOV .

recalls.Summary: Subaru of America, Inc. (Subaru) is recalling certain model year 2003-2004 Subaru Baja vehicles manufactured January 22, 2003, to July 21, 2004, 2004-2005 Impreza vehicles manufactured January 28, 2003, to May 31, 2005, 2003-2008 Subaru Legacy vehicles manufactured January 22, 2003, to May 2, 2008, 2003-2008 Subaru Outback vehicles manufactured February 18, 2003, to May 5, 2008, and 2005 Saab 9-2x vehicles manufactured February 11, 2004, to March 17, 2005.  The affected vehicles are equipped with a passenger side frontal air bag that may be susceptible to moisture intrusion which, over time, could cause the inflator to rupture upon its deployment.
recalls.Consequence: In the event of a crash necessitating deployment of the passenger's frontal air bag, the inflator could rupture with metal fragments striking the vehicle occupants potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
recalls.Remedy: Subaru will notify their owners and General Motors will notify Saab owners.  Dealers will replace the passenger air bag inflator, free of charge.    The Subaru recall began on June 17, 2015.  Owners may contact Subaru customer service at 1-800-782-2783.  The Saab recall began on July 27, 2015.  Owners of Saab vehicles may call 1-800-955-9007.  Subaru's number for this recall is WQR-53.  Note:  The recall completely supersedes recall 14V-399 (WQL-48) and partially supersedes recall 14V-763 (WQP-51) in that model year 2004 through 2005 Subaru Impreza and model year 2005 Saab 9-2x vehicles are now only part of this campaign.  Note: On December 18, 2015 Subaru informed NHTSA of an expansion of this recall to include certain model year 2003-2004 Subaru Baja, 2003-2008 Subaru Legacy and 2003-2008 Subaru Outback vehicles.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: ON CERTAIN PASSENGER SEDANS, WAGONS, AND SPORT UTILITY VEHICLES, THE CRUISE CONTROL CABLE COULD COME OUT OF ITS TRACK ON THE CRUISE CONTROL LEVER AND LODGE ON THE CONTROL LEVER TAB WHEN THE ACCELERATOR PEDAL IS RELEASED.  IF THIS CONDITION OCCURS, THE THROTTLE WILL NOT RETURN TO THE IDLE POSITION AND WILL REMAIN IN AN OPEN POSITION.
recalls.Consequence: IF THIS OCCURS DURING VEHICLE OPERATION, THE DRIVER COULD LOSE CONTROL OF THE VEHICLE, WHICH COULD RESULT IN A CRASH.
recalls.Remedy: DEALERS WILL INSTALL A CRUISE CONTROL CABLE RETAINING CLIP TO THE CRUISE CONTROL LEVER TAB ON THE THROTTLE SHAFT IN ORDER TO PREVENT THE CRUISE CONTROL CABLE FROM COMING OUT OF ITS TRACK.  OWNER NOTIFICATION BEGAN ON APRIL 12, 2004.  OWNERS SHOULD CONTACT  SUBARU AT 1-800-782-2783.
recalls.Notes: SUBARU RECALL NO. WWQ-01.  CUSTOMERS CAN ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S AUTO SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-888-DASH-2-DOT (1-888-327-4236).

recalls.Summary: ON CERTAIN PASSENGER AND SPORT UTILITY VEHICLES, THE COVER BOLTS FOR THE ENGINE  OIL CONTROL VALVE  MAY NOT BE SUFFICIENTLY TIGHTENED, ALLOWING OIL TO LEAK FROM AROUND THE COVER GASKET.
recalls.Consequence: IF LEAKING OIL CONTACTS COMPONENTS OPERATING AT HIGH TEMPERATURES, A FIRE COULD RESULT IN THE ENGINE COMPARTMENT.
recalls.Remedy: DEALERS WILL INSPECT AND RETIGHTEN THE OIL-FLOW CONTROL VALVE COVER BOLTS.  THE RECALL BEGAN ON OCTOBER 8, 2004.  OWNERS SHOULD CONTACT SUBARU AT 1-800-782-2783.
recalls.Notes: SUBARU RECALL NO. WWU-05.  CUSTOMERS CAN ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S AUTO SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-888-DASH-2-DOT (1-888-327-4236).

recalls.Summary: Subaru of America, Inc. (Subaru) is recalling certain 2004-2005 Impreza and WRX vehicles that received replacement front passenger air bag inflators under a previous recall.  The replacement air bag inflators may have been installed incorrectly.
recalls.Consequence: An incorrectly installed inflator may not properly inflate the passenger air bag, increasing the risk of injury during a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect the passenger inflator and if necessary, install a new inflator kit, free of charge.  Owner notification letters are expected to be mailed April 14, 2023.  Owners may contact Subaru's customer service at 1-844-373-6614.  Subaru's number for this recall is WRF-23.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

Rubber fuel lines under the intake manifold leak fuel when the temperature falls below 40 degrees F.  The smell permeates the cabin and fuel can be seen wetting nearby surfaces under the intake.  An inspection can be performed.  This represents a fire safety hazard that could occur while the vehicle is in motion, jeopardizing all surrounding traffic.  The problem is widely noted on Subaru internet forums, but only a recall for 2002-2003 models has been reported.  My car is a very early 2004, so it shares traits of the 2003 engines.  There are no warning lamps or notifications, only the smell of raw gas when the car starts and is in motion in winter temperatures.  This has happened repeatedly since the issue first occurred, so I avoid driving this vehicle if at all possible.

complaints.components: ENGINE AND ENGINE COOLING,POWER TRAIN,FUEL/PROPULSION SYSTEM
complaints.summary: UPON STARTING THE CAR DURING THE COLDER WINTER MONTHS, A RAW FUEL SMELL WILL BEGIN TO FILL THE CABIN IF THE HVAC SYSTEM IS TURNED ON TO VENT FRESH AIR.  THIS SMELL IS STRONG ENOUGH TO CAUSE LIGHTHEADEDNESS AND THE SENSATION OF NAUSEA.  UPON FURTHER INVESTIGATION, THE PASSENGER SIDE FUEL LINE IS LEAKING FUEL UNDERNEATH THE INTAKE MANIFOLD, TO THE EXTENT THAT YOU CAN VISIBLY SEE A PUDDLE OF FUEL BOILING ON TOP OF THE ENGINE BLOCK. THIS HAPPENS BECAUSE THERE ARE TWO HARD METAL FUEL LINES RUNNING TO THE FUEL INJECTORS CONNECTED BY A SMALL PIECE OF RUBBER HOSE WITH CLAMPS. HOWEVER THIS HOSE FROM THE FACTORY IS CUT TOO SHORT, SO WHEN THE TEMPERATURE IS COLD ENOUGH THE RUBBER LOOSES ITS ELASTIC PROPERTIES AND AS THE METAL LINES VIBRATE / MOVE WITH THE MOTOR, IT LEAKS FUEL OUT OF THE RUBBER HOSE.  THIS PROBLEM HAS BEEN ADDRESSED BY SUBARU IN THE TSB #09-36-03.  THEY OFFER TO REPLACE THE RUBBER HOSE AND HARD METAL FUEL LINE FOR MODEL YEARS 2002 AND 2003 IMPREZA WRX'S FREE OF CHARGE.  HAVING BEEN AN OWNER OF A 2002 IMPREZA WRX BEFORE PURCHASING MY 2004 IMPREZA WRX, I HAD THIS SERVICE PERFORMED AT MY LOCAL SUBARU DEALERSHIP.  I AM DISGUSTED TO FIND OUT THAT THIS COVERAGE DOES NOT APPLY TO THE MODEL YEAR 2004 IMPREZA WRX, WHEN IT FEATURES AN IDENTICAL MOTOR AND DRIVETRAIN TO THE PREVIOUS YEARS (2002, 2003.)  THIS MEANS THAT THE FUELING SYSTEM IS IDENTICAL AS WELL, AND THAT THE PREVIOUSLY ACKNOWLEDGED RAW FUEL LEAK IS HAPPENING IN MY CAR AS WELL.    THE FACT THAT THE 2004 IMPREZA WRX HAS THE SAME MOTOR. AND SAME FUEL SYSTEM, AND SUBARU OF AMERICA WILL OPENLY DENY COVERAGE TO HAVE THE PARTS REPLACED IS TRULY DISGUSTING IN ITSELF.  RAW FUEL LEAKING ON TOP OF A HOT ENGINE BLOCK, AROUND SOURCES OF IGNITION IS THE MOST EXTREME OF SAFETY HAZARDS, AND NOW I OWN A VEHICLE IN WHICH I CANNOT TRANSPORT MY WIFE AND CHILD.  I AM TRULY DISAPPOINTED IN SUBARU FOR TURNING A COLD SHOULDER TO THIS.  *TR

METAL CONNECTOR (THAT IS UNDER THE CAR CHASSIS) JOINING THE BRAKE PIPES (LINES) FOR THE REAR BRAKES RUSTED THROUGH.  WITH THE RUSTED CONNECTOR, BRAKE FLUID LEAKED THROUGH THE HOLES RESULTING TO BRAKES NOT TO ENGAGE AND STOP THE VEHICLE WHEN THE BRAKE PEDAL IS STEPPED ON.  BRAKE PEDAL WOULD BOTTOMED ALL THE WAY TO FLOOR  WHEN IT IS STEPPED ON.  FAILURE OF THE BRAKE CONNECTOR ALMOST RESULTED INTO THE REAR ENDING OF ANOTHER VEHICLE.  PICTURE OF THE RUSTED CONNECTOR IS AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.   *JS

I WAS INFORMED THAT THERE ARE TOO MANY VEHICLES TO BE INSPECTED AT THIS TIME FOR AN APPOINTMENT TO MADE, AND THAT WE WOULD RECEIVE A TELEPHONE CALL AT AN UNSPECIFIED TIME IN THE FUTURE WHICH WOULD THEN PERMIT US TO MAKE AN APPOINTMENT. WHAT IS THE POINT OF ISSUING RECALL NOTICES AND A PROCEDURE IN WHICH VEHICLES ARE TO BE INSPECTED WHEN THE DEALER REFUSES TO MAKE AN APPOINTMENT TO INSPECT THE VEHICLE?  *TR

complaints.components: ENGINE AND ENGINE COOLING,VEHICLE SPEED CONTROL
complaints.summary: STARTED AS AN UNUSUALLY HIGH IDLE WHILE IN PARK (AS SOON AS THE CAR WAS TURNED ON). AFTER A FEW HOURS OF RUNNING IT (DRIVING 48 MI TO WORK AND ERRANDS), I WOULD PUT THE CAR INTO DRIVE & AS SOON AS I WOULD REMOVE MY FOOT FROM THE BRAKE (ALREADY HAVING A HIGH IDLE) IT WOULD ACCELERATE ON IT'S OWN TO 15-20 MPH. WHEN I WOULD BRAKE AND BRING THE CAR TO A FULL STOP, IT WOULD "JUMP" SLIGHTLY AGAINST THE BRAKE. FINALLY I NOTICED THE GAS PEDAL FELT AS IF IT WAS NOT MOVING SMOOTHLY. AS I TOOK THE CAR OFF OF CRUISE CONTROL (AT 65 MPH) BY TURNING IT OFF AT THE CC CONTROLS ON THE WHEEL (MY FEET NOT NEAR THE PEDALS) IT BEGAN TO ACCELERATE RATHER THAN SLOW DOWN. AT THIS POINT I PARKED THE CAR & CALLED FOR A TOW TO THE SUBARU SERVICE CENTER.  *TR

I WAS DRIVING ON A MOUNTAIN ROAD AT ABOUT 50-55MPH WITH THE CRUISE CONTROL ON IN 5TH GEAR. WHEN I CAME TO A STEEP HILL THE CRUISE CONTROL OPENED THE THROTTLE WIDE OPEN TO MAINTAIN THE SET SPEED, WHEN THE CAR STARTED TO BOG DOWN I DECIDED TO SHIFT INTO 4TH GEAR. WHEN I PUSHED THE CLUTCH IN, THE CRUISE CONTROL  SHUT OFF BUT THE ENGINE REVVED TO 7000RPM AND STAYED THERE. I LET THE CLUTCH OUT TO PREVENT THE ENGINE FROM BEING DAMAGED AND USED MY BRAKED TO KEEP THE CAR AT ABOUT 55MPH UNTIL I CAME TO A STRAIGHT STRETCH OF ROAD THEN I PUSHED THE CLUTCH IN AND SHUT OFF THE IGNITION UNTIL THE ENGINE STOPPED. THIS WAS AT NIGHT SO WHEN THE IGNITION WAS SHUT OFF THE HEADLIGHTS WENT OFF TOO. FORTUNATELY THE ROAD WAS LIT UP ENOUGH TO SEE AND LITTLE TRAFFIC. A TOW TRUCK WAS CALLED OUT AND UPON INSPECTION THE DRIVER NOTICED A SILVER CLIP STUCK IN THE THROTTLE LINKAGE ASSEMBLY. HE REMOVED THE CLIP AND THE CAR WAS BACK TO NORMAL.   THE CLIP THAT WAS STUCK IN THE THROTTLE LINKAGE WAS PART OF A SERVICE BULLETIN/RECALL THAT SUBARU HAD PERFORMED ON MY 2004 IMPREZA WRX. IT WAS SUPPOSE TO PREVENT THE CRUISE CONTROL CABLE FROM COMING OUT OF ITS TRACK AND POSSIBLE BECOMING WEDGED IN THE THROTTLE LINKAGE CAUSING THE THROTTLE TO BE STUCK SOMEWHERE IN THE OPEN POSITION. THE CLIP THAT WAS TO PREVENT THIS CONDITION ACTUALLY BECAME THE PROBLEM.   THIS HAS ONLY HAPPENED  TO ME  THE ONE TIME ON 5/15/2010.  WHEN I GOT BACK HOME I TOOK THE CAR TO THE LOCAL SUBARU DEALER AND EXPLAINED WHAT HAD HAPPENED, THEY DIDN'T SEEM TOO CONCERNED. THEY WOULD NOT REPLACE THE CLIP SINCE THEY HAD DONE IT UNDER WARRANTY BACK IN 2005. THEY SAID I WOULD HAVE TO PAY FOR THE PARTS. NOT A REAL BIG DEAL TO ME SINCE THE CLIP WAS ONLY $1.67. THE REAL PROBLEM I HAD WAS THEY DIDN'T SEEM TOO CONCERNED THAT THE RECALL FIX BECAME THE PROBLEM THAT IT WAS SUPPOSE TO PREVENT.   I STILL HAVE THE OLD CLIP THAT POPPED OFF AND BECAME WEDGED IN THE THROTTLE LINKAGE.  THIS IS THE RECALL INFO I FOUND.  NHTSA CAMPAIGN ID NUMBER: 04V128000. *TR

1.AT ABOUT 12000 MILES,THE RIGHT REAR OF VEHICLE BEGAN TO MAKE A KNOCKING NOISE WHILE GOING OVER BUMPS,BRAKING OR ACCELERATING IS MORE EVIDENT AT LOW SPEEDS BUT IS STILL PRESENT AT HIGHER VELOCITIES.  2.THE FAILURE IS CURRENTLY STILL EXISTENT,THE RIGHT REAR OF VEHICLE HAS ABOUT 1/4 IN LOOSE PLAY BEFORE THE REAR STRUT BINDS. THIS AFFECTS HANDLING OF VEHICLE DURING TURNS OR EMERGENCY MANEUVERS AS THE SUSPENSION IS NOT WELL CONTROLLED BY STRUT BINDING. WHEN COMING TO A STOP,ONE CAN FEEL THE RIGHT REAR CORNER OF VEHICLE SETTLE AND HEAR A KNOCKING SOUND. THIS ISSUE TWICE SENT THE VEHICLE OUT OF CONTROL WHILE TURNING TO THE LEFT ON BUMPY ROADS AND FORTUNATELY NO ONE WAS INJURED AND NO DAMAGE WAS DONE. THIS DEFECT HAS BEEN TALKED ABOUT AT GREAT LENGTH IN VARIOUS SUBARU IMPREZA STI FORUMS AND IS REFERRED TO AS THE"REAR STRUT CLUNK" AND IT CAN AFFECTS BOTH SIDES OF VEHICLE. MODEL YEAR 2004 AND 2005 SUBARU IMPREZA STI ARE INVOLVED IN THIS. IT IS POSSIBLE THAT MY 2006 AND 2007 ARE AS WELL BUT I HAVEN'T CHECKED.  3.THE DEALER HAS REPLACED THE UPPER STRUT MOUNT A FEW TIMES TO NO AVAIL. THE DEFECTIVE PARTS ARE STILL ON THE VEHICLE. *TR

I WAS DRIVING MY 2004 SUBARU IMPREZA OUTBACK SPORT WHEN I HAD A FLAT TIRE (RIGHT REAR).  I CHANGED THE TIRE, USING THE "DONUT" IN THE CAR.  I DROVE ANOTHER 25 MILES NO FASTER THAN 40 MPH, AND US. SLOWER.  THEN A DRIVER BEHIND ME FLASHED HER LIGHTS SIGNALING ME TO STOP.  I STOPPED AND LEARNED MY CAR WAS BURNING UNDERNEATH, NEAR THE BACK.  WHEN I HAD THE CAR LOOKED AT, I FOUND THAT THE REAR DIFFERENTIAL WAS BADLY DAMAGED.  IN THE OWNER'S MANUAL, PERSONS WITH AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSIONS ARE INSTRUCTED TO USE A SWITCH TO TURN OFF THE AWD WHEN DRIVING ON THE "DONUT."  OTHERWISE, DAMAGE TO THE DIFFERENTIAL IS LIKELY.  HOWEVER, NO SUCH SWITCH EXISTS FOR CARS WITH MANUAL TRANSMISSIONS, WHICH I HAVE.  I FOLLOWED THE INSTRUCTIONS, NOT GOING MORE THAN 50 MPH OR MORE THAN 50 MILES ON THE DONUT.  BUT I DID EXTENSIVE DAMAGE ANYWAY, AND THE FIRE (WHICH WAS CAUSED BY THE HEAT OF THE DIFFERENTIAL SETTING THE UNDERCOATING ON FIRE) COULD HAVE BEEN DANGEROUS. *TR

2004 SUBARU IMPREZA WRX  ABS SYSTEM WILL NOT ALLOW SAFE STOPPING ON SNOW/SLEET/ICE. ON NOVEMBER 14, 2005, I TOOK THE CAR TO THE SUBARU DEALER. I TOLD THEM THAT I THOUGHT THE SYNCHRONIZERS WERE BAD IN 2ND AND 4TH GEARS. MY THEORY IS THAT WHEN TURNING THE CARS AND SHIFTING, THERE IS TWISTING IN THE DRIVETRAIN THAT IS BRINGING THE SYNCHRONIZERS IN CONTACT WITH THE TRANSMISSION CASE CAUSING THE INITIAL DAMAGE. THE SENSOR'S WILL THEN NOT ALIGN THE GEARS PROPERLY AND THEN THE GRINDING STARTS. THE MORE THE CAR IS DRIVEN, THE MORE THE SENSOR'S ARE DAMAGED, AND, THUS, THE MORE THE GEARS GRIND. THE POINT IS THAT ALL SUBSEQUENT DAMAGE CAUSED BY THE DAMAGED SENSORS, DUE TO FAULTY DESIGN, SHOULD BE COVERED BY THE WARRANTY. SUBARU NEEDS TO BE INVESTIGATED CONCERNING THIS PROBLEM. issues.title: Ringland Failure and Piston Damage
issues.description: The EJ257 engine in the GD STI is prone to ringland failure, where the thin metal between the piston ring grooves cracks or breaks, leading to catastrophic engine damage. This is often caused by detonation from poor fuel quality, aggressive tuning, or lean running conditions.
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild or replacement with forged pistons and proper tuning
issues.prevention: Use high octane fuel, avoid aggressive tuning without supporting modifications, regular oil changes, proper engine break-in

issues.title: Turbocharger Failure
issues.description: The IHI VF39 turbocharger commonly fails due to oil starvation, dirty oil, or excessive boost pressure. Banjo bolt filters can clog, restricting oil flow to the turbo.
issues.fix_description: Replace turbocharger, clean or replace banjo bolt filters, check oil lines
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper grade oil, allow turbo cooldown before shutdown, replace banjo bolt filters

issues.title: Transmission Synchronizer Wear
issues.description: The 6-speed manual transmission suffers from premature synchronizer wear, particularly in 2nd and 3rd gears, causing difficult shifting and grinding noises.
issues.fix_description: Transmission rebuild with new synchronizers and proper fluid
issues.prevention: Use proper transmission fluid, avoid aggressive shifting when cold, double-clutch if necessary

issues.title: Head Gasket Failure
issues.description: External head gasket leaks are common, particularly on the driver's side, causing coolant and oil leaks. Internal failures can also occur leading to coolant in oil.
issues.fix_description: Replace head gaskets, machine heads if warped, replace timing belt and water pump
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, avoid overheating, use proper coolant mixture

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: The in-tank fuel pump can fail prematurely, especially under high-demand conditions or when fuel levels are consistently low, leading to fuel starvation.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly, check fuel filter and lines
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank above 1/4 full, use quality fuel, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: Center Differential Failure
issues.description: The center differential can fail due to abuse, improper tire sizing, or lack of maintenance, causing AWD system malfunction and potential drivetrain damage.
symptoms: grinding noises from center of car
issues.fix_description: Replace center differential, ensure proper fluid levels and tire matching
issues.prevention: Use matching tires, regular differential service, avoid extended driving on spare tire

issues.title: Knock Sensor Failure
issues.description: Knock sensors can fail or become less sensitive over time, leading to improper timing advance and potential engine damage from undetected detonation.
issues.fix_description: Replace knock sensors, clear ECU codes, verify proper installation and wiring
issues.prevention: Use high quality fuel, avoid carbon buildup, regular maintenance

issues.title: Clutch Premature Wear
issues.description: The stock clutch is marginal for the engine's torque output and can wear prematurely, especially with performance modifications or aggressive driving.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch disc, pressure plate, and release bearing with upgraded components
issues.prevention: Avoid riding clutch, proper shifting technique, consider upgrade if modified

issues.title: Exhaust Manifold Cracking
issues.description: The up-pipe and exhaust manifolds are prone to cracking due to heat cycling and thermal stress, leading to exhaust leaks and potential turbo damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace cracked manifold or up-pipe, consider upgrading to aftermarket units
issues.prevention: Allow proper warm-up and cool-down cycles, avoid rapid temperature changes

issues.title: Intercooler End Tank Failure
issues.description: The plastic end tanks on the top-mount intercooler can crack or fail, especially under high boost conditions or with age, causing boost leaks.
issues.fix_description: Replace intercooler or repair end tanks, upgrade to front-mount intercooler
issues.prevention: Monitor boost levels, avoid excessive boost pressure, regular inspection

issues.title: Timing Belt Tensioner Issues
issues.description: The timing belt tensioner can fail prematurely, leading to timing belt slack and potential interference engine damage if the belt skips or breaks.
issues.fix_description: Replace timing belt, tensioner, idler pulleys, and water pump as preventive maintenance
issues.prevention: Follow manufacturer timing belt service intervals, inspect tensioner regularly

editorial.tagline: Rally-bred fury in a practical package
editorial.hero_blurb: The GD-generation STI represents Subaru's rally dominance distilled into street form. This is the car that brought World Rally Championship technology to your driveway, complete with Brembo brakes and a differential arsenal that defies physics.
editorial.essence: The GD STI is pure motorsport DNA wrapped in everyday usability. It's the last of the truly analog performance Subarus, delivering unfiltered communication between driver and machine through every input.
editorial.heritage: Born from Subaru's WRC success in the early 2000s, the GD STI carried forward the legacy of the legendary 22B while introducing the larger 2.5L EJ257 engine. This generation cemented the STI's reputation as the thinking enthusiast's rally weapon.
editorial.design_philosophy: Function over form defines every line and vent. Subaru's engineers prioritized aerodynamic efficiency, cooling, and weight distribution over styling trends, creating a purposeful aesthetic that screams performance intention.
editorial.motorsport_history: Direct descendant of Petter Solberg's 2003 WRC championship-winning machine. The GD platform dominated rally stages worldwide and spawned numerous special editions celebrating Subaru's motorsport victories.
editorial.engine_character: The EJ257 delivers explosive mid-range torque with a characteristic flat-four growl. Power builds aggressively from 3,000 RPM, creating an addictive surge that rewards committed throttle application.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 6-speed manual offers precise, mechanical shifts with short throws and positive engagement. Each gear change feels purposeful and direct, connecting you intimately to the drivetrain's every movement.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Razor-sharp turn-in combined with AWD traction creates cornering confidence that borders on supernatural. The chassis communicates every surface change while maintaining composure through the most challenging terrain.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic rack delivers pure, unfiltered feedback with perfect weight progression. You feel every pebble, every grip level change, every subtle chassis movement through the wheel with crystalline clarity.
editorial.brake_confidence: Brembo 4-piston front calipers provide incredible stopping power with progressive pedal feel. These brakes inspire complete confidence whether attacking mountain roads or navigating daily traffic.
editorial.sound_signature: Distinctive boxer rumble escalates to an angry snarl under boost. The exhaust note is unmistakably Subaru - a deep, mechanical symphony that announces your presence without apology.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who crave uncompromising performance with daily usability. Perfect for enthusiasts who appreciate mechanical honesty and aren't afraid of hands-on maintenance.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Luxury seekers expecting refinement or those wanting low-maintenance ownership. The STI demands respect, attention, and regular mechanical sympathy.

expertReviews.verdict: The 2007 WRX STI is described as 'almost unbeatable' with an incredible sound, iconic design, and solid GD chassis. While it has excellent all-wheel drive and makes great turbo noises, it suffers from factory understeer, high center of gravity, and cheap interior. Best suited for rallying rather than road racing, but modifications can unlock its potential.

expertReviews.verdict: The 2003 Subaru Impreza WRX STI 'Blobeye' represents the sweet spot of the WRX STI lineup, offering forged internals from factory, incredible tunability, and genuine WRC heritage in a more refined package than the GC8. With modifications producing 400hp at all four wheels, it delivers exceptional performance while remaining practical as a daily driver. The reviewer emphasizes its engaging driving experience, excellent AWD system, and timeless design. However, rising values and basic interior quality are noted drawbacks. Clay concludes this is a future classic that enthusiasts should acquire soon before prices become truly unobtainable.

expertReviews.title: Subaru WRX vs STI - 3 Reasons Why The WRX Is Better
pros: Lighter weight (100-200 lbs less)
Better low-end torque delivery with peak torque at 2000 RPM vs 4000 RPM
More fuel efficient with better range
Same 0-60 time as STI
Better value for money
cons: Rev hang makes shifting less smooth
expertReviews.verdict: For most buyers, the WRX is the better choice due to its lighter weight, superior low-end torque delivery, better fuel economy, and lower price. The STI is only recommended for serious track use or heavy modification plans, as its advantages don't justify the $8000 price premium for street driving.

cons: Ugly design with cheap-looking plastic cladding

Manual transmission can't be equipped with performance upgrades
Economy car roots are apparent throughout
Only 3 more horsepower than previous generation
expertReviews.verdict: The 2022 WRX maintains the classic WRX formula with punchy turbocharged power, all-wheel drive, and rally inspiration. Despite being heavier with minimal power gains, it matches previous generation performance while being more livable daily. The design is polarizing and cheap-looking, but the driving experience remains engaging and capable. A solid final generation before the likely EV transition.
